I fly out next week for this amazing tattoo conference we put together!! I’m so excited to be a part of an educational retreat for queer and ally tattooers! For this event, I'm a producer, committee organizer, graphic designer, copywriter, talent booker and so much more all as a volunteer 😅😅 It's been exhausting, and time-consuming but I'm so proud. Everyone involved has worked to extreme levels of dedication and could of not have happened without each person's efforts.

I’m excited to see how this goes!!! 🤞If we blow it I’m very proud of our efforts to change the tattoo industry for the better and I’m stoked we tried! Hopefully, it inspires more people to create queer events, and learning environments for their community and to make tattooing day-to-day FUN, inspiring, and filled with love and support.

I’m thankful for all the experiences and skills I've accumulated in my life that are going towards this and that are being put to use (and put to the test) to create this! I'm thankful for my time on the Queer tattoo alliance committee, The Tattoo education video cast @liveinthecastrotattoo with @reinventingthetattoo , the Castro district's merchants board where I served as secretary and VP, all my trips to city college learning graphic design, business and animation, going to tattoo conferences, teaching my seminar, 17 years of tattooing and of course running @castrotattoo as a business owner has taught me so much!

@queercation_tattoo 
🌈🌈🌈 I’m so excited 😆

I’ll be interviewed Tomorrow 8am PST on Reinventing the Tattoo’s tattoo weekly show (link in bio) @reinventingthetattoo 

“Haley Adams has been making their mark on the tattoo industry in unique ways over their 18 years of tattooing, from owning and running their historical queer tattoo shop in San Francisco CA “Castro Tattoo”, their interview channel
on Reinventing the Tattoo “Live in the Castro” where they interview the minorities of the industry like LGBTQ+, BIPOC and women tattooers, and recently organized the first queer and ally tattoo conference “Queercation” where around 65 tattooers took advanced seminars and gained inspiration for 3 days in New Mexico!”

Help me decide 🤔

I have to say this has been the most incredible year, there’s the bad and the good but my heart is so full! 
So grateful for meeting my friend Mar @spitepiss & starting our moped crew, the best buds ever😍😭

I threw a queer and ally tattoo conference for education, skill sharing and inspiration for this amazing queer tattoo community thats growing 😭🥰😭 @queercation_tattoo 

I bought an apartment in San Francisco through the low to medium income program and I love so much! All artists live in my building and it’s so magical.

I left the continent for the first time and traveled to Spain!!

I met this amazing woman Katie @mskatielou who’s my girlfriend 🤯 she’s so cool and impressive! I can just be 100% myself around her and she really likes it! ❤️🥲

My friends and coworkers continue to be a huge ol light in my life and I have no idea what I would do without such sweet inspirational people in my life!!!! 
I love being at Castro Tattoo @castrotattoosf and tattooing toooo 😭😭
